{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3239064,"name":"joel truher","username":"truher","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/truher/{size}/172222_2.png","created_at":"2023-10-10T21:13:58.182Z","cooked":"<p>Hi everybody,</p>
<p>We continue to have trouble with the java process lifecycle, which results in the symptom of a “zombie” state: robot communication works but the controls don’t.  Investigating these cases, we find two copies of the java process running on the RIO, and we can fix the problem via ssh:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">killall -9 java
</code></pre>
<p>(…or by rebooting the RIO, which is easier.)</p>
<p>I noticed that GradleRIO and DeployUtils already try two different ways to kill the java process, which makes me suspicious that this isn’t a completely unique problem.</p>
<p>I added a third in <code>build.gradle</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">deploy {
    targets {
        roborio(...) {
            ...
            artifacts {
                ...
                killKillKill(getArtifactTypeClass('CommandArtifact')) {
                    command = 'killall -9 java'
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>This command appears to run (at least gradle says it does), but it doesn’t seem to help.</p>
<p>Does anyone have any suggestions for making this sort of process-killer effective?  Note that all <em>three</em> methods are failing in these cases, but the ssh method does work.  Am i using the CommandArtifact correctly?</p>
<p>I thought the problem might be an extra log we’re writing – like one of the threads might spend a fair amount of time in uninterruptible sleep waiting for the file to close, but removing the extra log writer didn’t help.  We also use the DataLogManager, which I suppose might be busy writing a lot.  I’m under the impression that the kernel would queue the signal anyway, so it would die upon completing whatever system thing it was busy with.  And it definitely does eventually complete, as proven by the manual “ssh” killall solution above.</p>
<p>Anyway at this point I don’t care why it’s hanging, i just want the <code>killKillKill</code> command to succeed.</p>
<p>Any ideas?</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2023-10-10T21:13:58.182Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":26,"reads":117,"readers_count":116,"score":153.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":442138,"topic_slug":"terminating-the-java-process","display_username":"joel truher","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53190,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/terminating-the-java-process/442138/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3239067,"name":"Thad House","username":"Thad_House","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/a4c791/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-10-10T21:33:38.236Z","cooked":"<p>If you run with --info, it will show what the result of that kill command is.</p>
